$Yadier Molina's ball bounced and struck signage above and behind the LF wall; that area is out of play; the ball was ruled in play and Matt Carpenter scored the apparent game-ending run when he should have been stopped at 3B; the umpires left the field and then Reds manager Bryan Price ran after them trying to challenge the play; Price had not moved to the top step of the dugout to signal a possible challenge

replay,7,moliy001,SLN,vanol901,STL10,,Y,M,PIT,S $Yadier Molina's hit to LF bounced out of play and struck the railing behind the wall; the ball caromed back onto the field and was ruled in play; no Pirates player retrieved the ball but the ball dude ran onto the field to pick it up; Molina scored on the play; Pirates manager Clint Hurdle challenged the in play ruling; the call was overturned by replay to an automatic double, since the ball struck something off the field of play
$Cardinals sent Matt Holliday, who is unlikely to return, to LF where he received a standing ovation and was then replaced by Tommy Pham
